There are growing calls for the government to secure COVID-19 vaccines for South Africa. Professor Shabir Madhi from the Wits University's Vaccines and Infectious Diseases Analytics Research Unit spoke with eNCA's Shahan Ramkissoon. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Oxford-AstraZeneca vaccine is best suited for Africa according to Professor of Vaccinology at the University of the Witwatersrand, Shabir Madhi. Professor Madhi is leading the clinical trial of the vaccine locally. READ: COVID-19: AstraZeneca president discusses their vaccine He said the vaccine isn't only effective but also affordable. The Oxford vaccine is so far reported to have a good safety record with no serious side-effects. The ongoing late-stage trial is taking place at 150 global sites in the US, Germany, Turkey, South Africa, Brazil and Argentina. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs